On Wed, 15 May 2002, Sharpe, Steven (Facilities Planning) wrote:

> Has anyone ever tried to find a locking gas cap for the 71 style. Actually
> it appears that a locking gas cap can't be made for this type of filler.
>
> This leads me to my next question. Has anyone ever fabricated a lock for the
> filler door?
>
You could take a new cap, weld a piece of strap metal to it, then mount a
corresponging piece of strap metal to one of the flange bolts below the
cap.  Put a hole in each and install a padlock throught the holes to
prevent the cap from being turned.

George Lyle

